<p class="mb-4 text-xl">Every great life-changing discovery begins the same way—with new knowledge. It can change everything, from a single life to the future of entire communities. That’s why academic medicine, and the continuous pursuit of knowledge, is at the center of everything we do. The Medical College of Wisconsin brings a synergy between the best medical education, research and patient care. Tomorrow’s discoveries happen right here alongside the very people who bring those lessons to our trainees. Every bit of knowledge, and every advancement, provides our students with an unprecedented, collaborative learning environment, and helps improve the vitality and care of our communities.</p>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl">MCW’s Office of Postdoctoral Education is among the oldest in the United States (est. 2001). Our Postdoc Office is housed within the Graduate School and serves all postdoctoral researchers on campus, affirming our philosophy that postdocs are, first and foremost, trainees.</p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-xl mb-8">
	<li>Approximately 200 postdocs train at MCW each year</li>
	<li>Postdocs can be members of 22 Clinical, 7 Basic Science departments, 17 Centers and 2 Institutes.</li>
	<li>3rd largest private medical school in the USA </li>
	<li>More than 1200 active clinical trials </li>
	<li>$1.96 billion in research funding over the last 10 years </li>
</ul>

