<h2 class="font-bold text-2xl mb-4">What sets the Medical College of Wisconsin apart?  </h2>
<p class="mb-4 text-xl">The primary goal of the MCW Office of Postdoctoral Education is to grow and foster our postdoc community. The office provides equitable support and unique resources, programs, and professional development training for MCW postdocs. The activities sponsored by the Postdoc Office are designed to complement the excellent training and mentorship provided by our outstanding faculty.  </p>

<div class="px-16"><img class="max-w rounded overflow-hidden shadow-xl bg-whitep mb-8 md:float-right md:max-w-md md:ml-8" src="/img/mcw-lab.jpg" alt="Scientists"></div>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>The MCW Office of Postdoctoral Education provides a large range of award opportunities including:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-xl mb-8">
<li>Excellence in Science (top postdoc each year) </li>
<li>Outstanding Woman Postdoc</li>
<li>Postdoc paper of the season (Fall and Spring competitions) </li>
<li>Postdoc Professional Development Award (Fall and Spring competitions) </li>
<li>Postdoc Faculty Mentor of the Year</li>
<li>Annual Scientific Image Award</li>
</ul>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>Some additional unique facts about MCW for prospective postdocs:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-xl mb-8">
<li>MCW postdocs are eligible to apply for 4 internal funding mechanisms as PI (total funding of nearly $1 million per year) to support their independent research and training endeavors</li>
<li>The Medical College of Wisconsin has strong ties to industry/start-up companies in Greater Milwaukee, the primary industry hub in the state of Wisconsin </li>
<li><a href="https://www.mcw.edu/departments/catalyst-bioconsulting">MCW’s Catalyst BioConsulting</a> allows postdocs the opportunity to gain valuable consulting experience with local start-up companies while still a postdoc </li>
<li>MCW requires postdoc salaries to be at or above NIH guidelines </li>
<li>All postdocs are required to complete a Career Development Plan (and meet with advisors to discuss) on a yearly basis </li>
<li>Monthly “Spotlight on Science” professional development seminar brings a large range of external speakers/panelists to campus </li>
<li>Annual Postdoc Research Symposium provides a forum for postdocs to gain valuable scientific feedback from the entire institution </li>
<li>Immigration Office includes dedicated staff to help foreign national postdocs with visa issues </li>
<li><a href="https://www.mcw.edu/education/office-of-postdoctoral-education/postdoc-advisory-committee">Postdoc Advisory Committee</a> (group of ~20 current postdocs) works closely with the Postdoc Office to gain leadership experience </li>
<li>Postdoc-specific courses include “Advance from Postdoc to Faculty”, “Learn to Teach”, “Transition from Postdoc to Industry”, “Career Advancement Pathway Workshop”, and others </li>
<li>Large range of social, community-building events exclusively for postdocs on a monthly basis throughout the year </li>
</ul>
